# Reports

This folder contains scan and analysis outputs for each tool.  
Add your raw outputs, exported files, and short analysis notes into the appropriate subfolder.

Structure:
- `/reports/nmap/` — `.nmap`, `.xml`, `.gnmap` outputs and notes
- `/reports/wireshark/` — `.pcap`, `.pcapng` and capture analysis notes
- `/reports/hashcat/` — `potfile`, cracked-results, logs
- `/reports/sqlmap/` — sqlmap output files, dumps and notes

**Reminder:** Only include outputs from authorized tests. Do not upload sensitive or personally identifiable data.
git checkout -b feature/add-reports
mkdir -p reports/nmap reports/wireshark reports/hashcat reports/sqlmap

cat > reports/README.md <<'EOF'
# Reports

This folder contains scan and analysis outputs for each tool.  
Add your raw outputs, exported files, and short analysis notes into the appropriate subfolder.

Structure:
- /reports/nmap/ — .nmap, .xml, .gnmap outputs and notes
- /reports/wireshark/ — .pcap, .pcapng and capture analysis notes
- /reports/hashcat/ — potfile, cracked-results, logs
- /reports/sqlmap/ — sqlmap output files, dumps and notes

**Reminder:** Only include outputs from authorized tests. Do not upload sensitive or personally identifiable data.
EOF

# create placeholders so folders are tracked
touch reports/nmap/.gitkeep
touch reports/wireshark/.gitkeep
touch reports/hashcat/.gitkeep
touch reports/sqlmap/.gitkeep

git add reports
git commit -m "Add reports folder structure and placeholders"
git push -u origin feature/add-reports
